<paragraph id="3952CB318CFF49FDA74CECC372FB50F4" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
In males, 
<taxonomicName id="D2DE337215B5274ECF31CFFAB1795BFA" genus="A." lsidName="A. sparsipunctata" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="sparsipunctata">
<emphasis id="FB2E1EE7C2C44C8636389B097F7EE67D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">A. sparsipunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognised by the shape of the labrum which is wide and rectangular (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E37BFCD6B58712AD517A890187B54FDE" captionStart="Figures 21–28" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 21 - 28. Andrena (Campylogaster) sparsipunctata sp. nov. 21 male profile 22 male genitalia 23 male face and labrum 24 male tergites. Andrena (Campylogaster) pruinosa succinea Dours, 1872 25 male face and labrum 26 male tergites. Andrena caroli Perez, 1895 27 male face and labrum 28 male tergites." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.974.54794.figures21-28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/460645" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">23</figureCitation>
), whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="761CF831A14881DD6A8A2D1D2BBA18D5" genus="A." lsidName="A. pruinosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="pruinosa">
<emphasis id="1FCCDDD8C649E7C5565AB89E3ED8DDF2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">A. pruinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is trapezoidal and markedly emarginate (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="242934204B3F22FB1E76410FC6032165" captionStart="Figures 21–28" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 21 - 28. Andrena (Campylogaster) sparsipunctata sp. nov. 21 male profile 22 male genitalia 23 male face and labrum 24 male tergites. Andrena (Campylogaster) pruinosa succinea Dours, 1872 25 male face and labrum 26 male tergites. Andrena caroli Perez, 1895 27 male face and labrum 28 male tergites." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.974.54794.figures21-28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/460645" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">25</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName id="1F6FA330AC2BF5ED96DDFA7620A48A62" genus="A." lsidName="A. caroli" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="caroli">
<emphasis id="1A7BE5E6EFF2BD5AAB6614A3C64C35E7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">A. caroli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is less strongly trapezoidal and emarginate (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1A127103471D57A0E2DE501BB695C91F" captionStart="Figures 21–28" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 21 - 28. Andrena (Campylogaster) sparsipunctata sp. nov. 21 male profile 22 male genitalia 23 male face and labrum 24 male tergites. Andrena (Campylogaster) pruinosa succinea Dours, 1872 25 male face and labrum 26 male tergites. Andrena caroli Perez, 1895 27 male face and labrum 28 male tergites." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.974.54794.figures21-28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/460645" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">27</figureCitation>
), but the tergites have well-marked and dense bands of short white hairs on the tergal margins (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="13710B6CEAB1F07BF2814F9ECCD9021C" captionStart="Figures 21–28" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 21 - 28. Andrena (Campylogaster) sparsipunctata sp. nov. 21 male profile 22 male genitalia 23 male face and labrum 24 male tergites. Andrena (Campylogaster) pruinosa succinea Dours, 1872 25 male face and labrum 26 male tergites. Andrena caroli Perez, 1895 27 male face and labrum 28 male tergites." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.974.54794.figures21-28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/460645" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">28</figureCitation>
), whereas 
<taxonomicName id="1AF4D9706C5583DAD1F286BCF47DE330" genus="A." lsidName="A. sparsipunctata" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="sparsipunctata">
<emphasis id="8F5A9E1B4DFB9B40E87A2B65FA84C12C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">A. sparsipunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has only a few scattered hairs on the tergal margins, never forming well-marked bands, as in 
<taxonomicName id="A29FFC08306A67268EC113BB4920D8A6" genus="A." lsidName="A. pruinosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="pruinosa">
<emphasis id="B3D0FD3111678BC2A05A2165A5DBDF91" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">A. pruinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="DA5FBC7BC0C62876F526436D7E9B5DF7" captionStart="Figures 21–28" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 21 - 28. Andrena (Campylogaster) sparsipunctata sp. nov. 21 male profile 22 male genitalia 23 male face and labrum 24 male tergites. Andrena (Campylogaster) pruinosa succinea Dours, 1872 25 male face and labrum 26 male tergites. Andrena caroli Perez, 1895 27 male face and labrum 28 male tergites." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.974.54794.figures21-28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/460645" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">26</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
